{"title_page": "Singapore Mediation Convention", "text_new": "{{Infobox Treaty\n| name                = Singapore Convention on Mediation\n| long_name           = United Nations Convention on International Settlement Agreements Resulting from Mediation\n| image               = Singapore Mediation Convention.svg\n| caption             =States that signed the convention (yellow)\n| date_drafted        =\n| date_signed         = 7 August 2019 (first signatories)\n| location_signed     = [[Singapore]]\n| date_sealed         =  20 December 2018 (adopted by the UN)\n| date_effective      = Not in force\n| condition_effective = 3 ratifications\n| date_expiration     =\n| signatories         =51<ref name=rat>{{cite web|url=https://treaties.un.org/pages/ViewDetails.aspx?src=TREATY&mtdsg_no=XXII-4&chapter=22&clang=_en|title=United Nations Convention on International Settlement Agreements Resulting from Mediation|accessdate=17 August 2019|publisher=[[United Nations Treaty Series]]}}</ref>\n| parties             = None\n| depositor           = [[Secretary-General of the United Nations]]\n| languages           = Arabic, Chinese, English, French, Russian, and Spanish\n| website             =\n| wikisource          = \n}}\nThe '''Singapore Convention on Mediation''', formally the '''United Nations Convention on International Settlement Agreements Resulting from Mediation''' which was adopted on 20 December 2018 and opened for signature on 7 August 2019<ref>{{cite news |title=U.N. members sign mediation convention to settle trade disputes |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-un-convention-singapore/u-n-members-sign-mediation-convention-to-settle-trade-disputes-idUSKCN1UX093 |work=Reuters |date=7 August 2019 |language=en}}</ref>, is an [[international agreement]] regarding the recognition of [[mediation|mediated settlements]]. Following the [[UN General Assembly]] adopting it on 18 December 2018, the Convention was opened for signature by all States as of 7 August 2019, when it was signed by 46 states.<ref name=rat/>\n\n==List of States Signatory to the Convention==\nAs of 25 February 2020, 51 states have signed the convention and 2 states have ratified it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uncitral.un.org/en/texts/mediation/conventions/international_settlement_agreements/status|title=Status: United Nations Convention on International Settlement Agreements Resulting from Mediation|accessdate=20 November 2019|publisher=[[United Nations Commission on International Trade Law]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-fiji-instruments-ratification-convention-mediation-12471112|title=Singapore, Fiji first 2 countries to deposit instruments of ratification for Singapore Convention on Mediation|accessdate=26 February 2020|publisher=[[CNA (news channel)|CNA]]}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Country !! signature !! ratification !! entry into force\n|-  \n| {{flag|Afghanistan}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Armenia}} || {{dts|26 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Belarus}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Belize}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Brunei}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Chad}} || {{dts|26 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|-\n| {{flag|Chile}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|China}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Colombia}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Republic of the Congo}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Ecuador}} || {{dts|25 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|-\n| {{flag|Kingdom of Eswatini}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Fiji}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||{{dts|25 February 2020}}||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Gabon}} || {{dts|25 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|-\n| {{flag|Georgia}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Grenada}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- 