article/us-un-convention-singapore/u-n-members-sign-mediation-convention-to-settle-trade-disputes-idUSKCN1UX093 |work=Reuters |date=7 August 2019 |language=en}}</ref>, is an [[international agreement]] regarding the recognition of [[mediation|mediated settlements]]. Following the [[UN General Assembly]] adopting it on 18 December 2018, the Convention was opened for signature by all States as of 7 August 2019, when it was signed by 46 states.<ref name=rat/>\n\n==List of States Signatory to the Convention==\nAs of 25 February 2020, 51 states have signed the convention and 2 states have ratified it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uncitral.un.org/en/texts/mediation/conventions/international_settlement_agreements/status|title=Status: United Nations Convention on International Settlement Agreements Resulting from Mediation|accessdate=20 November 2019|publisher=[[United Nations Commission on International Trade Law]]}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-fiji-instruments-ratification-convention-mediation-12471112|title=Singapore, Fiji first 2 countries to deposit instruments of ratification for Singapore Convention on Mediation|accessdate=26 February 2020|publisher=[[CNA]]}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Country !! signature !! ratification !! entry into force\n|-  \n| {{flag|Afghanistan}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Armenia}} || {{dts|26 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Belarus}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Belize}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Brunei}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Chad}} || {{dts|26 September 2019}} ||- ||-\n|-\n| {{flag|Chile}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|China}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Colombia}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Republic of the Congo}} || {{dts|7 August 2019}} ||- ||-\n|- \n| {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}} || {{dts|7 August